{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019JPUnLmZESWPTn6xeXG1Jz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { defineConfig, devices } from \"@playwright/test\";\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Playwright config for local E2E integration tests.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * Runs against a local solana-test-validator with real wallet mode.\n     7→ * The validator + program deploy is handled by external bootstrap scripts;\n     8→ * this config only starts the Vite dev server.\n     9→ */\n    10→export default defineConfig({\n    11→  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n    12→  fullyParallel: false,\n    13→  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,\n    14→  retries: 0,\n    15→  workers: 1,\n    16→  reporter: \"list\",\n    17→  timeout: 60_000,\n    18→\n    19→  use: {\n    20→    baseURL: \"http://localhost:3002\",\n    21→    screenshot: \"off\",\n    22→    trace: \"retain-on-failure\",\n    23→    ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"],\n    24→    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },\n    25→  },\n    26→\n    27→  projects: [\n    28→    {\n    29→      name: \"local-e2e\",\n    30→      testMatch: \"local/**/*.spec.ts\",\n    31→      use: { ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"], viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 } },\n    32→    },\n    33→  ],\n    34→\n    35→  webServer: {\n    36→    command: \"npx vite --port 3002\",\n    37→    url: \"http://localhost:3002\",\n    38→    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,\n    39→    timeout: 30_000,\n    40→    env: {\n    41→      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",\n    42→      VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\",\n    43→      VITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\",\n    44→      VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK: \"localnet\",\n    45→    },\n    46→  },\n    47→});\n    48→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0196NStvkAvhRuEYBCVbHJxk","session_id":"4693177a-8d7b-4a03-b79e-8bfa2852241e","uuid":"c5af3b85-1361-4759-a57b-463727354ee1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017kkoTrtsmyrigbPaaF3pGV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have both files in full. Here's a summary of what I found:\n\n## File 1: `lifecycle.spec.ts`\nThis is a complete end-to-end test covering the full coinflip flow:\n- **Create** (Player A creates a match, iron tier, heads)\n- **Join** (Player B joins the match)\n- **Resolve** (VRF fulfills with pre-loaded HEADS result → Player A wins)\n- **Claim** (Player A claims payout, match closed)\n- **Verify** (Checks treasury fees, player profile deltas, and match state)\n\n**Key details:**\n- Uses two isolated browser contexts (playerAPage, playerBPage)\n- Entry amount: 5,000,000 lamports (0.005 SOL)\n- Creator wins because they chose HEADS and the mock VRF data returns HEADS (byte[0] = 2)\n- Asserts player stats: totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon\n- Asserts 3% fee goes to treasury\n- No unhandled console errors in either browser context\n\n## File 2: `chain.ts`\nThis is the transaction builder module with these key functions:\n\n**Query functions:**\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches()` — Get matches in \"waiting\" phase\n- `fetchClaimableMatches()` — Get unclaimed matches where player is creator or opponent\n- `fetchMatchByCreator()` — Get a single match by creator's public key\n- `fetchMatch()` — Get a match by match PDA\n\n**Instruction builders:**\n- **`buildCreateMatchTx()`** — Create a new match (tier, side)\n- **`buildJoinMatchTx()`** — Join an existing match (sets up Orao VRF request)\n- **`buildCancelMatchTx()`** (lines 374–395) — Cancel a match (creator only, presumably \"waiting\" phase)\n- **`buildTimeoutCancelTx()`** (lines 397–425) — Cancel due to VRF timeout (any caller)\n- **`buildClaimPayoutTx()`** — Claim payout after settlement\n\n**Key for your task:**\nThe `buildCancelMatchTx()` function is simple — it calls `program.methods.cancelMatch()` with just the creator, match PDA, and system program. No Orao accounts needed. This is the cancel operation you'll implement in the Anchor instruction."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a68878461434b53d0 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35547\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 10345</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4693177a-8d7b-4a03-b79e-8bfa2852241e","uuid":"3dabc0cd-aa1c-4558-93f4-ae42c20ee739","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files in full and return their complete content:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` - existing lifecycle E2E test\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` - transaction builders (look for buildCancelMatchTx and any cancel-related functions)\n\nI need the complete content of both files.","agentId":"a68878461434b53d0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have both files in full. Here's a summary of what I found:\n\n## File 1: `lifecycle.spec.ts`\nThis is a complete end-to-end test covering the full coinflip flow:\n- **Create** (Player A creates a match, iron tier, heads)\n- **Join** (Player B joins the match)\n- **Resolve** (VRF fulfills with pre-loaded HEADS result → Player A wins)\n- **Claim** (Player A claims payout, match closed)\n- **Verify** (Checks treasury fees, player profile deltas, and match state)\n\n**Key details:**\n- Uses two isolated browser contexts (playerAPage, playerBPage)\n- Entry amount: 5,000,000 lamports (0.005 SOL)\n- Creator wins because they chose HEADS and the mock VRF data returns HEADS (byte[0] = 2)\n- Asserts player stats: totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon\n- Asserts 3% fee goes to treasury\n- No unhandled console errors in either browser context\n\n## File 2: `chain.ts`\nThis is the transaction builder module with these key functions:\n\n**Query functions:**\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches()` — Get matches in \"waiting\" phase\n- `fetchClaimableMatches()` — Get unclaimed matches where player is creator or opponent\n- `fetchMatchByCreator()` — Get a single match by creator's public key\n- `fetchMatch()` — Get a match by match PDA\n\n**Instruction builders:**\n- **`buildCreateMatchTx()`** — Create a new match (tier, side)\n- **`buildJoinMatchTx()`** — Join an existing match (sets up Orao VRF request)\n- **`buildCancelMatchTx()`** (lines 374–395) — Cancel a match (creator only, presumably \"waiting\" phase)\n- **`buildTimeoutCancelTx()`** (lines 397–425) — Cancel due to VRF timeout (any caller)\n- **`buildClaimPayoutTx()`** — Claim payout after settlement\n\n**Key for your task:**\nThe `buildCancelMatchTx()` function is simple — it calls `program.methods.cancelMatch()` with just the creator, match PDA, and system program. No Orao accounts needed. This is the cancel operation you'll implement in the Anchor instruction."}],"totalDurationMs":10345,"totalTokens":35547,"totalToolUseCount":2,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10396,"cache_read_input_tokens":24569,"output_tokens":575,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10396,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KVd19hbV6Z2eRhqTLXYnVz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the complete contents of all four files:\n\n## 1. page-objects.ts\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts`\n\nProvides reusable page object helpers for coinflip E2E tests. Includes:\n- **Selector constants** (`sel`): CSS classes for lobby, sidebar, tier/side selectors, match cards, active match view, results\n- **Type definitions**: `CoinSide` (\"heads\" | \"tails\"), `Tier` (iron, bronze, silver, gold, platinum, diamond)\n- **Navigation**: `navigateToCoinflip()`\n- **Actions**: `selectTier()`, `selectSide()`, `createMatch()`, `joinMatch()`, `cancelMatch()`, `claimOrSettle()`, `backToLobby()`\n- **Wait/Assert primitives**: `waitForPhaseLabel()`, `waitForResult()`, `waitForLobbyMatch()`, `assertLobbyEmpty()`, `assertErrorToast()`, `assertNoErrorToast()`, `getSolBalance()`, `trackConsoleErrors()`, `waitForText()`, `waitForLobby()`\n\nAll functions use Playwright's `Page` and `Locator` APIs with explicit timeouts.\n\n---\n\n## 2. on-chain.ts\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts`\n\nRPC-based on-chain assertion helpers. Includes:\n- **Program IDs & Constants**: `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`, `PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID`, `FEE_BPS` (300 bps = 3%)\n- **PDA Derivation**: `getMatchPda()`, `getConfigPda()`, `getPlayerProfilePda()`\n- **Program Instances**: `getCoinflipProgram()`, `getPlatformProgram()` (read-only via Anchor)\n- **Account Types**: `MatchAccount`, `PlayerProfileAccount` interfaces\n- **Fetch Helpers**: `fetchMatch()`, `fetchPlayerProfile()`, `getTreasuryAddress()`\n- **Balance Helpers**: `getBalanceLamports()`, `snapshotBalance()`\n- **Fee Calculation**: `calculateExpectedFee()` (mirrors on-chain logic)\n- **Assertions**: `assertMatchCreated()`, `assertMatchClosed()`, `assertTreasuryFee()`, `assertPlayerProfile()`, `assertPlayerProfileDelta()`, `snapshotPlayerProfile()`\n\n---\n\n## 3. wallets.ts\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts`\n\nDeterministic wallet-funding helper. Includes:\n- **Deterministic Keypairs**: `PLAYER_A` and `PLAYER_B` (fixed Uint8Array seeds `0xaa` and `0xbb`)\n- **Constants**: `LOCAL_RPC_URL` (\"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"), `DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL` (10)\n- **Functions**:\n  - `fundWallet()`: Airdrop SOL to a single wallet and confirm\n  - `fundTestWallets()`: Fund both players, sanity-check balances, return keypairs + connection\n\n---\n\n## 4. fixtures.ts\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts`\n\nDual-browser-context Playwright fixture. Includes:\n- **Interface**: `DualPlayerFixtures` with:\n  - `playerAContext`, `playerBContext` (isolated BrowserContext)\n  - `playerAPage`, `playerBPage` (Page instances)\n  - `playerAKeypair`, `playerBKeypair` (Keypair objects)\n  - `connection` (shared RPC Connection)\n- **Helper**: `createPlayerContext()` injects keypair seed via `addInitScript()` so TestWalletProvider picks it up\n- **Fixture Exports**: Extended test harness with all fixtures wired; re-exports `expect` from Playwright\n\nThis enables two isolated browser contexts in a single test, each with its own keypair injected before page load."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9b82c8ba34b0353b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39953\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 13440</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4693177a-8d7b-4a03-b79e-8bfa2852241e","uuid":"229abf55-0871-47e8-8ccf-a87415b90674","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore these files and return their full content:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` - page object helpers\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` - on-chain assertion helpers\