{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0196NStvkAvhRuEYBCVbHJxk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the complete contents of both files:\n\n## 1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Localnet setup helper — initializes coinflip and platform configs.\n *\n * Must be called once before the E2E suite starts, after the test validator\n * is running and wallets are funded. Initializes:\n * - Coinflip config PDA (sets authority + treasury)\n * - Platform config PDA (sets authority + treasury)\n */\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  PublicKey,\n  SystemProgram,\n  Transaction,\n  sendAndConfirmTransaction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport {\n  CoinflipIDL,\n  PlatformIDL,\n  type Coinflip,\n  type Platform,\n} from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport { LOCAL_RPC_URL } from \"./wallets\";\n\n// ── Deterministic admin/treasury keypairs ──────────────────────────────\nconst SEED_ADMIN = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xdd);\nconst SEED_TREASURY = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xcc);\n\nexport const ADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_ADMIN);\nexport const TREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_TREASURY);\n\n// ── Program IDs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n\nfunction getConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getPlatformConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"platform_config\")],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction makeProvider(connection: Connection, wallet: Keypair): AnchorProvider {\n  return new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {\n      publicKey: wallet.publicKey,\n      signTransaction: async (tx) => {\n        tx.partialSign(wallet);\n        return tx;\n      },\n      signAllTransactions: async (txs) => {\n        txs.forEach((tx) => tx.partialSign(wallet));\n        return txs;\n      },\n    },\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n  );\n}\n\n/**\n * Initialize both program configs and fund the admin/treasury accounts.\n * Idempotent: silently succeeds if configs already exist.\n */\nexport async function initializeLocalnet(\n  rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const connection = new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n\n  // Fund admin and treasury\n  await Promise.all([\n    fundIfNeeded(connection, ADMIN.publicKey, 2),\n    fundIfNeeded(connection, TREASURY.publicKey, 2),\n  ]);\n\n  const provider = makeProvider(connection, ADMIN);\n  const coinflipProgram = new Program(\n    CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip,\n    provider,\n  );\n  const platformProgram = new Program(\n    PlatformIDL as Idl as Platform,\n    provider,\n  );\n\n  // Initialize coinflip config (idempotent)\n  const configPda = getConfigPda();\n  const configExists = await connection.getAccountInfo(configPda);\n  if (!configExists) {\n    const ix = await coinflipProgram.methods\n      .initializeConfig(TREASURY.publicKey)\n      .accountsStrict({\n        authority: ADMIN.publicKey,\n        config: configPda,\n        systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      })\n      .instruction();\n\n    const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n    await sendAndConfirmTransaction(connection, tx, [ADMIN], {\n      commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Initialize platform config (idempotent)\n  const platformConfigPda = getPlatformConfigPda();\n  const platformConfigExists =\n    await connection.getAccountInfo(platformConfigPda);\n  if (!platformConfigExists) {\n    const ix = await platformProgram.methods\n      .initializePlatform(TREASURY.publicKey)\n      .accountsStrict({\n        authority: ADMIN.publicKey,\n        config: platformConfigPda,\n        systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      })\n      .instruction();\n\n    const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n    await sendAndConfirmTransaction(connection, tx, [ADMIN], {\n      commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nasync function fundIfNeeded(\n  connection: Connection,\n  pubkey: PublicKey,\n  solAmount: number,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const balance = await connection.getBalance(pubkey);\n  if (balance >= solAmount * 1_000_000_000) return;\n\n  const sig = await connection.requestAirdrop(\n    pubkey,\n    solAmount * 1_000_000_000,\n  );\n  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n  await connection.confirmTransaction(\n    { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n    \"confirmed\",\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## 2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig, devices } from \"@playwright/test\";\n\n/**\n * Playwright config for local E2E integration tests.\n *\n * Runs against a local solana-test-validator with real wallet mode.\n * The validator + program deploy is handled by external bootstrap scripts;\n * this config only starts the Vite dev server.\n */\nexport default defineConfig({\n  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n  fullyParallel: false,\n  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,\n  retries: 0,\n  workers: 1,\n  reporter: \"list\",\n  timeout: 60_000,\n\n  use: {\n    baseURL: \"http://localhost:3002\",\n    screenshot: \"off\",\n    trace: \"retain-on-failure\",\n    ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"],\n    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },\n  },\n\n  projects: [\n    {\n      name: \"local-e2e\",\n      testMatch: \"local/**/*.spec.ts\",\n      use: { ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"], viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 } },\n    },\n  ],\n\n  webServer: {\n    command: \"npx vite --port 3002\",\n    url: \"http://localhost:3002\",\n    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,\n    timeout: 30_000,\n    env: {\n      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",\n      VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\",\n      VITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\",\n      VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK: \"localnet\",\n    },\n  },\n});\n```\n\nBoth files are complete. The first is a localnet initialization helper that sets up Coinflip and Platform config PDAs and funds admin/treasury accounts. The second is a Playwright configuration for local E2E testing that runs against a local Solana validator with real wallet mode disabled (test wallet enabled instead)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3013a5b7bbf62942 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31244\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 16239</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4693177a-8d7b-4a03-b79e-8bfa2852241e","uuid":"8d2abe7b-048b-4187-b447-49b932f28b60","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files in full and return their complete content:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` - localnet initialization helper\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` - playwright local config\n\nI need the complete content of both files.","agentId":"a3013a5b7bbf62942","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the complete contents of both files:\n\n## 1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Localnet setup helper — initializes coinflip and platform configs.\n *\n * Must be called once before the E2E suite starts, after the test validator\n * is running and wallets are funded. Initializes:\n * - Coinflip config PDA (sets authority + treasury)\n * - Platform config PDA (sets authority + treasury)\n */\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  PublicKey,\n  SystemProgram,\n  Transaction,\n  sendAndConfirmTransaction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport {\n  CoinflipIDL,\n  PlatformIDL,\n  type Coinflip,\n  type Platform,\n} from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport { LOCAL_RPC_URL } from \"./wallets\";\n\n// ── Deterministic admin/treasury keypairs ──────────────────────────────\nconst SEED_ADMIN = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xdd);\nconst SEED_TREASURY = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xcc);\n\nexport const ADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_ADMIN);\nexport const TREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_TREASURY);\n\n// ── Program IDs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n\nfunction getConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getPlatformConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"platform_config\")],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction makeProvider(connection: Connection, wallet: Keypair): AnchorProvider {\n  return new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {\n      publicKey: wallet.publicKey,\n      signTransaction: async (tx) => {\n        tx.partialSign(wallet);\n        return tx;\n      },\n      signAllTransactions: async (txs) => {\n        txs.forEach((tx) => tx.partialSign(wallet));\n        return txs;\n      },\n    },\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n  );\n}\n\n/**\n * Initialize both program configs and fund the admin/treasury accounts.\n * Idempotent: silently succeeds if configs already exist.\n */\nexport async function initializeLocalnet(\n  rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const connection = new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n\n  // Fund admin and treasury\n  await Promise.all([\n    fundIfNeeded(connection, ADMIN.publicKey, 2),\n    fundIfNeeded(connection, TREASURY.publicKey, 2),\n  ]);\n\n  const provider = makeProvider(connection, ADMIN);\n  const coinflipProgram = new Program(\n    CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip,\n    provider,\n  );\n  const platformProgram = new Program(\n    PlatformIDL as Idl as Platform,\n    provider,\n  );\n\n  // Initialize coinflip config (idempotent)\n  const configPda = getConfigPda();\n  const configExists = await connection.getAccountInfo(configPda);\n  if (!configExists) {\n    const ix = await coinflipProgram.methods\n      .initializeConfig(TREASURY.publicKey)\n      .accountsStrict({\n        authority: ADMIN.publicKey,\n        config: configPda,\n        systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      })\n      .instruction();\n\n    const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n    await sendAndConfirmTransaction(connection, tx, [ADMIN], {\n      commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Initialize platform config (idempotent)\n  const platformConfigPda = getPlatformConfigPda();\n  const platformConfigExists =\n    await connection.getAccountInfo(platformConfigPda);\n  if (!platformConfigExists) {\n    const ix = await platformProgram.methods\n      .initializePlatform(TREASURY.publicKey)\n      .accountsStrict({\n        authority: ADMIN.publicKey,\n        config: platformConfigPda,\n        systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      })\n      .instruction();\n\n    const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n    await sendAndConfirmTransaction(connection, tx, [ADMIN], {\n      commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nasync function fundIfNeeded(\n  connection: Connection,\n  pubkey: PublicKey,\n  solAmount: number,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const balance = await connection.getBalance(pubkey);\n  if (balance >= solAmount * 1_000_000_000) return;\n\n  const sig = await connection.requestAirdrop(\n    pubkey,\n    solAmount * 1_000_000_000,\n  );\n  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n  await connection.confirmTransaction(\n    { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n    \"confirmed\",\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## 2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig, devices } from \"@playwright/test\";\n\n/**\n * Playwright config for local E2E integration tests.\n *\n * Runs against a local solana-test-validator with real wallet mode.\n * The validator + program deploy is handled by external bootstrap scripts;\n * this config only starts the Vite dev server.\n */\nexport default defineConfig({\n  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n  fullyParallel: false,\n  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,\n  retries: 0,\n  workers: 1,\n  reporter: \"list\",\n  timeout: 60_000,\n\n  use: {\n    baseURL: \"http://localhost:3002\",\n    screenshot: \"off\",\n    trace: \"retain-on-failure\",\n    ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"],\n    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },\n  },\n\n  projects: [\n    {\n      name: \"local-e2e\",\n      testMatch: \"local/**/*.spec.ts\",\n      use: { ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"], viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 } },\n    },\n  ],\n\n  webServer: {\n    command: \"npx vite --port 3002\",\n    url: \"http://localhost:3002\",\n    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,\n    timeout: 30_000,\n    env: {\n      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",\n      VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\",\n      VITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\",\n      VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK: \"localnet\",\n    },\n  },\n});\n```\n\nBoth files are complete. The first is a localnet initialization helper that sets up Coinflip and Platform config PDAs and funds admin/treasury accounts. The second is a Playwright configuration for local E2E testing that runs against a local Solana validator with real wallet mode disabled (test wallet enabled instead)."}],"totalDurationMs":16239,"totalTokens":31244,"totalToolUseCount":2,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4721,"cache_read_input_tokens":24549,"output_tokens":1967,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4721,"ephemeral_5m_input